docs.text:
PyMapManager is a Python package to analyze time-series image stacks.


PyMapManager opens annotations created with the Igor Pro version of 
Map Manager
. Allowing additional analysis to easily be performed.


There are three components to PyMapManager:




PyMapManager Python Package. See the 
API Documentation


PyMapManager server. See the 
server documentation


PyMapManager desktop application. See the 
github repository




PyMapManager Python package


See the 
/examples
 folder in the main GitHub repository for example Python code to easily perform additional analysis.


PyMapManager server


The PyMapManager server allows web-based browsing of annotations and stacks.






PyMapManager deskop application


The Qt version of PyMapManager is a desktop application
